						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged at the end. It records an endowment of 10(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruviśalūr-Perumāṉ at Amaninārāyaṇachaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> village on the northern bank of the river, by <hi rend="bold">Rājēndraśōḻa-Mūvēnda[vēḷār]</hi> of Miḻalai-kūṟṟam, probably an officer of <hi rend="bold">Rājēndra-Chōḷa I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
